# Trivy ignore file — documented vulnerability acceptance for the production images.
#
# Policy: every FIXABLE and/or runtime-reachable advisory is fixed at the source
# (Dockerfile + lockfiles): Debian `apt upgrade`, npm CLI bump to a version with
# patched vendored deps, `ws` override to 8.21.0, and removal of the vulnerable
# esbuild binary that vite pins. Only advisories that are BOTH (a) not fixable
# without a breaking Strapi-5 change and (b) unreachable on the production
# `strapi start` / SSR request path are listed below. A CRITICAL is never ignored.
# Last reviewed: 2026-06-19.

# vite 5.4.x — `server.fs.deny` bypass on Windows alternate data-stream paths.
# Reachable ONLY through the vite *dev server* on *Windows*. Production runs on
# Linux and never starts the vite dev server: the admin panel is pre-built in the
# image's builder stage, and `strapi start` only loads vite's JS through the CLI
# module graph, never serving files through it. The fix is vite >=6.4.3, a major
# bump pinned transitively by Strapi 5 (@strapi/admin) that cannot be applied
# without a breaking Strapi upgrade.
CVE-2026-53571

# esbuild 0.27.7 (pulled in by esbuild-loader) — missing binary integrity check
# in esbuild's *Deno* module loader (lib/deno/mod.ts) while downloading the
# native binary from an npm registry. Applies only when esbuild is consumed via
# the Deno loader; this image runs on Node.js and never uses Deno, and
# esbuild-loader is build-time webpack tooling that is not on the `strapi start`
# request path. Fixed in esbuild 0.28.1 — already the resolved top-level version;
# only esbuild-loader keeps a 0.27.7 copy that Strapi 5's tree pins.
GHSA-gv7w-rqvm-qjhr

# nodemailer 8.0.5 (pinned by @strapi/provider-email-nodemailer@5.x) — the
# message-level `raw` option bypasses disableFileAccess/disableUrlAccess. Reachable
# ONLY if the application passes a `raw` message to the email provider. Star Sign's
# email path (newsletter double-opt-in + contact via Brevo SMTP) only ever sends
# standard fields (from/to/subject/text/html) — it never sets `raw`, so the
# advisory is not exploitable here. Fixed in nodemailer 9.0.1, a major bump that
# @strapi/provider-email-nodemailer pins to 8.0.5 and cannot be forced without a
# breaking change to the production email channel. The undici advisory shipped in
# the same scan IS fixed at source (cheerio->undici override to ^7.28.0).
GHSA-p6gq-j5cr-w38f
